
This is some more information on XTR and its upgrades.

XTreme Racing Data-Disks ReadMe
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

>> Requirements <<

The original XTreme Racing!


>> The XTR Data-Disk Set comprises <<


·  The XTreme Racing update patch
·  The XTreme Racing track editor
·  20 all new tracks


>> The XTreme Racing update patch <<


Please read the "Upgrade.Readme" text file for full details of the upgrade
patch.


>> The XTreme Racing track editor <<


·  Create your own tracks, or modify existing tracks - all aspects can be
   changed, including the graphics
·  Fully OS3 compliant - yes, you can multitask and use it on gfx boards 
   and set the number of colours to use etc...
·  Friendly and Intuitive to use - standard Amiga menus with keyboard 
   short-cuts. Full set of preferences
·  Include all your own graphics, from the tiles to the objects - you can change 
   the lot
·  Replace any or all of the existing sound fx with your own custom sound fx
·  Track layout is done by placing tiles upon a simple grid
·  Full on-line help included plus quick start guide
·  Layout all the track boundaries, computer car routes, drop down points, 
   surfaces (inc. jumps, water, etc), secret paths, etc...


>> XTR Extra Tracks <<


There are 5 completely new tile and objects graphic sets included on the
data-disks.
The new tracks now feature more objects than before.  These objects 
include such delights as Elvis, putrefying corpses, football fans and LOADS
of others!
In all there are 20 new tracks (12 Race, 3 Bonus and 5 Deathmatch)!!!!

There are now 3 new cups (Kiwi, Hot Leather and Double D), and 1 new season
(Maniac GrandPRIX).

The new tile sets are:

·	Hell Below
·	Lurve Land
·	Gothic City
·	Duplo Bricks Land
·	Space Port


